President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. has declared a major disaster for the Muscogee (Creek) Nation due to severe storms, tornadoes, and flooding that occurred from May 2 to May 8, 2022. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement the Tribal Nation's response and recovery efforts. Federal funding will be available on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Roland W. Jackson has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made if requested by the Tribal Nation and warranted by damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.